<item>
            <title>[LU-4405] stat degradation (interoperability bug after landing a LU-3240)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4405</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cray reported an stat performance degradation in master with older servers (pre &amp;lt; 2.4).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it&apos;s easy replicated with statmany tool, as now it&apos;s have only ~600 stats per second for same files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;after bisect search by Cray &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Patrick Farrell: http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/6460/8/lustre/mdc/mdc_locks.c
Patrick Farrell: That&apos;s the patch that my bisection suggests is the problem
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;after looking to logs - i see more getattr rpc&apos;s as should be in such situation.&lt;br/&gt;
so root cause of additional RPC&apos;s - patch tries to match PERM bit in lock for servers don&apos;t supported such feature, after disabling it - stat rate is restored.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>any client with &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/6460/8/&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/6460/8/&lt;/a&gt; patch landed.</environment>
